title: Major upsets in legislative races as results trickle in
author: NJ Spotlight News
description:
Senate President Steve Sweeney could be the most potentially shocking upset from the general election, but he’s not the only Democratic legislator in trouble. In the lower half of his ticket, Democratic Assemblymen John Burzichelli and Adam Taliaferro could both lose. Upsets are also looming in other districts.
